              "fontWeight": "700"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "x9mvGQ",
              "name": "Frame 51",
              "width": 706,
              "stroke": {
                "align": "inside",
                "thickness": 1
              },
              "gap": 15,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "g7ouG9",
                  "name": "01",
                  "opacity": 0,
                  "fill": [
                    "#ffffffff",
                    {
                      "type": "gradient",
                      "gradientType": "linear",
                      "enabled": true,
                      "rotation": -450,
                      "size": {
                        "height": 1
                      },
                      "colors": [
                        {
                          "color": "#b5d3e9ff",
                          "position": 0
                        },
                        {
                          "color": "#cc9d96ff",
                          "position": 1
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "content": "01",
                  "lineHeight": 1.075,
                  "fontFamily": "Rounded Mplus 1c Bold",
                  "fontSize": 40,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": -8.4
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "Smc7L",
                  "name": "Rather than designing screen by screen, I built a modular design system in Figma reusable components and patterns that turned a 2-week sprint into something structured and repeatable. The web product couldn't simply be resized for mobile. I rearchitected the entire flow from scratch with a mobile-first lens, simplifying navigation and interactions that would have collapsed on a small screen. With no existing brand to pull from, I established a visual language early in the design phase – typography, colour, and iconography rooted in what Kad Pekerja Madani was meant to represent. This gave every screen a foundation instead of a blank canvas. Alongside all of this, a live developer handoff kept design and build running in parallel so nothing was waiting on anything.",
                  "fill": "#e0e0e0ff",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Rather than designing screen by screen, I built a modular design system in Figma reusable components and patterns that turned a 2-week sprint into something structured and repeatable.\n\nThe web product couldn't simply be resized for mobile. I rearchitected the entire flow from scratch with a mobile-first lens, simplifying navigation and interactions that would have collapsed on a small screen.\n\nWith no existing brand to pull from, I established a visual language early in the design phase – typography, colour, and iconography rooted in what Kad Pekerja Madani was meant to represent. This gave every screen a foundation instead of a blank canvas.\n\nAlongside all of this, a live developer handoff kept design and build running in parallel so nothing was waiting on anything.",
                  "fontFamily": "Satoshi",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
